  <h2>What to Look for in an AI Humanizer</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bypass rate</strong> — the only metric that truly matters. Test it against the specific detector you need to pass.</li>
    <li><strong>Output quality</strong> — does the humanized text still make sense and sound natural?</li>
    <li><strong>Free tier</strong> — can you test it before paying?</li>
    <li><strong>Word limit</strong> — how much can you humanize per session or per month?</li>
    <li><strong>Speed</strong> — how quickly does it process your text?</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips for Getting the Best Results</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Always run your text through the humanizer twice for best results</li>
    <li>Check the output for quality before submitting — occasionally review the text manually</li>
    <li>Use the academic or professional style setting for formal documents</li>
    <li>For very long documents, break them into sections of 500 words or less</li>
    <li>Always verify the final output with a free detector like GPTZero before submitting</li>
  </ul>

